latestPosts.caption:
As a young multi-hyphenate of modern India, Gauravi Kumari is creating a legacy of her own – not just as a curator and patron of Indian craft, but as an active participator in taking Jaipur’s heritage and culture, global.

This May, we’re diving into the era of the multi-hyphenate – individuals who wear many hats and redefine success on their own terms. From beauty conversations between mothers and daughters to signs of a fashion recession and how it’s shaping style today, this issue explores identity, inheritance, and everything in between.

Gauravi is wearing a tulle insert knit dress, ‘Galaxie Monogram’ necklace, ‘Majestic’ ring, all @louisvuitton

Catch all the behind-the-scenes action from our May cover shoot with Gauravi Kumari dressed in looks from @louisvuitton

Video: @abhishek.trived1 

#GraziaIndia #GauraviKumari #Gauravi #MayCover #2025 #2025Cover

“I think I always look to them [her family, her mother Diya Kumari and grandmother, (Rajmata) Padmini Devi] and how they effortlessly managed to stay modern yet totally rooted,” says Kumari, explaining her balancing act. “And for me too, whether it’s in my projects or my personal life, I’ve always wanted to stay rooted in them and have conversations on how to make it relevant and stay modern. I’m very proud of my heritage and I would like that balance in all my ventures.” 

Gauravi is wearing a Leather accent dress, ‘Tumbler’ earrings, ‘Majestic’ ring, all @louisvuitton

latestPosts.caption:
For The Palace Atelier’s SS25 collection, we wanted to shine a light on all the spaces, details, and stories that make the City Palace special — it’s our Ode to the Palace.

The @msmsmuseum is naturally, at the heart of everything we do as a museum store. Be it the Painting & Photography Gallery which contain centuries worth of artwork, or the hues of the Chhavi Niwas, every corner of the Museum tells a generations-old tale. 

We also wanted to spotlight the people of the Palace; the ladies and the guards who are the heart and soul of this historic space. 

With this collection, we want to bring all of those stories, to you. The past, the present, and the future of the Palace.

The Palace Atelier, in its entirety, is a love letter to the City Palace, and Jaipur. We’re so excited to share this collection with you 💗

latestPosts.caption:
Princess Gauravi Kumari (@gauravikumari) wears her legacy like a couture gown—refined for every era. A scion of a royal lineage where women have long embraced a broader vision, she champions the hands that create. Through global and local collaborations rooted in heritage and excellence, she leads with foresight and flair—whether at The Palace Atelier or through the initiatives of PDKF at the City Palace, Jaipur. Our April–May cover star also graces this issue in stunning fashion cameos—each a quiet whisper of elegance passed down through generations.

Head over to the link in bio to read the full story.
